WEBVTT

00:01.730 --> 00:10.824
At this time, we will have our first split sermon of the service by Mr. Ken Barton entitled, Let's Seek God Now.

00:11.385 --> 00:11.966
Mr. Barton?

00:22.141 --> 00:27.990
Before I start my message, I wanted to share a praise item.

00:28.611 --> 00:30.354
Paul Hammond is

00:30.530 --> 00:34.233
a friend of ours that we ask for prayer last Sabbath.

00:35.094 --> 00:42.221
And he has had surgery for cancer in this area.

00:43.102 --> 00:53.151
And he's off the ventilator, and he's talking, both of which they weren't sure, and even less sure about the talking part.

00:53.592 --> 01:00.338
But anything he's doing well, pray is God for that.

01:00.450 --> 01:03.594
Thank you all for the prayers, and thank God most of all.

01:12.406 --> 01:20.116
I'm betting everybody has noticed that there's an undeclared war going on in the world.

01:22.419 --> 01:27.986
Many are worried about what may happen, and of course that would be rightly so.

01:29.378 --> 01:40.216
Rather than just giving into that, I want to speak today to what we can do that will make a difference by following Isaiah's advice.

01:41.538 --> 01:48.610
Many are concerned with the direction in which our nation and in the fact the world is headed.

01:49.352 --> 01:55.602
Many agree that our nation and the world is going downhill at an alarming rate.

01:57.410 --> 02:01.897
But there are areas where we disagree, areas such as, is there any hope?

02:06.844 --> 02:13.714
Is there anything that can be done or do we just need to get ready and write out the horrible end time events?

02:15.417 --> 02:21.806
So Isaiah 55, 6, and 7, seek the Lord while He may be found.

02:22.908 --> 02:24.811
Call upon Him while He is near.

02:25.852 --> 02:26.994
That would like me now.

02:28.194 --> 02:29.075
in my opinion.

02:29.535 --> 02:33.199
Let the wicked forsake his way in the unrighteous man his thoughts.

02:33.900 --> 02:41.529
Let him return to the Lord and he will have mercy on him and to our God for he will abundantly pardon.

02:42.850 --> 02:51.520
I've heard people who will say they'll be glad when the Lord returns so that we won't have to put up with the evil things that are being done in this world.

02:52.360 --> 02:57.426
Of course, there's a lot that's going to be.

02:58.850 --> 03:02.776
They're not looking at what happens in between now and getting there.

03:02.796 --> 03:05.821
I can understand it though.

03:06.381 --> 03:22.546
It would be so wonderful to live in peace and not have to worry about being robbed, attacked, swindled, and you wouldn't have to worry about some of the stuff you have to worry about responding to that.

03:24.189 --> 03:27.794
Look at how much advertising is done just on the topic

03:27.906 --> 03:29.148
of identity theft.

03:30.029 --> 03:32.693
The thing is, we're not there yet.

03:34.396 --> 03:41.727
But I'm betting there are many who are possibly realizing that perhaps they should wake up and maybe pay attention.

03:42.588 --> 03:43.670
Life is uncertain.

03:43.970 --> 03:44.672
I get that.

03:45.873 --> 03:48.077
Scripture acknowledges that time and again.

03:48.137 --> 03:54.807
For instance, Luke 1239 in the New King James Version, Jesus gives some very solid advice.

03:55.889 --> 03:56.850
But know this.

03:57.250 --> 04:06.161
that if the master of the house had known what hour the thief would come, he would have watched and not allowed his house to be broken into.

04:06.181 --> 04:16.895
If I didn't know when that guy was going to pull out in front of me, I would have moved over into the other lane or just slowed down.

04:20.540 --> 04:25.426
That's a reference thing of rec we had a while that several years ago.

04:28.674 --> 04:37.891
There's a reason that God tells us over and over again that we need to be mindful of bad things that can happen.

04:38.912 --> 04:41.738
We need to be mindful of our relationship with Him.

04:41.778 --> 04:50.834
He's calling us all the time to be near to Him.

04:57.410 --> 05:03.337
He's telling us that we need to get ourselves in a right relationship with Him while there's still time.

05:05.160 --> 05:09.145
So let's go back just a few verses starting at verse 35 in Luke.

05:09.785 --> 05:26.386
Let your waste begirded and your lamps burning, and you yourselves be like men who wait for their master when he will return from the wedding that when he comes and knocks, they may open to him immediately.

05:29.922 --> 05:34.570
Blessed are those servants whom the master, when he comes, will find watching.

05:35.211 --> 05:42.484
Assuredly, I say to you that he will gird himself and have him sit down to eat and will come and serve them.

05:42.524 --> 05:50.638
And if he should come in the second watch or come in the third watch and find them so, blessed are those servants.

05:50.658 --> 05:55.506
If that's not a warning to keep our eyes open and pay attention, I don't know what is.

05:56.290 --> 06:00.736
These days, we have wondrous communications capabilities.

06:02.057 --> 06:11.750
We have telephones, internet, smartphones, email, texting, Twitter accounts, Facebook, other applications like that.

06:12.591 --> 06:19.239
You know, if you can't find out what's going on somewhere, you're not paying a lot of attention, I guess.

06:19.259 --> 06:21.522
I don't know, which sometimes I'm not.

06:23.585 --> 06:24.786
If there's a problem,

06:25.666 --> 06:35.558
I'm sorry, many people have phones provided by their jobs.

06:35.879 --> 06:39.764
One of the things about all this is we can keep in touch with our family.

06:40.264 --> 06:48.815
We can teach with our friends, even folks we only know through certain applications, but we can help each other.

06:49.496 --> 06:51.578
We can lift them up when they're having problems.

06:51.618 --> 06:54.482
They can lift us up when we're having problems.

06:55.554 --> 07:01.682
If there's a problem, then there are ways to address it.

07:02.223 --> 07:06.969
When it comes to our relationship with God, He has an even better way.

07:08.211 --> 07:08.531
Prayer.

07:08.591 --> 07:11.715
It doesn't require a phone.

07:11.735 --> 07:13.257
It doesn't require a computer.

07:14.259 --> 07:15.520
You don't need batteries.

07:16.682 --> 07:19.465
You don't need anything except a right spirit.

07:20.807 --> 07:22.930
We can speak to God anytime.

07:24.290 --> 07:26.953
and he always wants to hear from us.

07:29.275 --> 07:33.219
Now there are some stipulations as to our conversations.

07:33.940 --> 07:39.085
We need to come to him in a correct manner and attitude.

07:39.565 --> 07:47.533
We need to come realizing that this is the master and creator of all that is.

07:49.435 --> 07:52.338
That's who we're coming before.

07:55.682 --> 07:59.428
Through Him, everything that is is.

08:01.831 --> 08:05.256
First, though, coming to God requires faith.

08:05.837 --> 08:12.627
Hebrews 11-1, now faith is a substance of things hoped for, the evidence of things not seen.

08:13.909 --> 08:17.134
For by it, the elders obtained a good testimony.

08:17.595 --> 08:22.322
By faith, we understand that the worlds were framed by the Word of God.

08:22.946 --> 08:27.292
so that the things which are seen were not made of things which are visible.

08:29.635 --> 08:34.561
But without faith, it is impossible to please him.

08:35.062 --> 08:43.973
For he who comes to God must believe that he is and that he is a rewarder of those who diligently seek him.

08:45.355 --> 08:48.519
The key is to seek him now.

08:50.261 --> 08:50.802
Second,

08:51.682 --> 09:20.562
Chronicles 7, 14, if my people who are called by my name shall humble themselves and pray and seek my face and turn from their wicked ways, then I will hear from heaven and will forgive their sin and will heal their land.

09:22.626 --> 09:27.410
That's the kind of difference we want to happen in our lives.

